<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    Phase E.5 A3 (closure, 2026-06-02) — corrected prune of duplicate
    dn_item_data_map rows. v1 of this prune
    (lc-muw-2026-06-02-prune-dn-item-data-map-duplicates.xml) had TWO
    independent bugs that each individually broke it:

      1. The preCondition was inverted: it expected the sqlCheck to
         return 0 (no duplicates) for the changeset to fire. On every
         fresh `docker compose down -v && up --build` the precondition
         failed and onFail="MARK_RAN" marked the changeset as executed
         without running the DELETE.

      2. The DELETE referenced an `id` column on dn_item_data_map.
         That column doesn't exist — the schema is a pure
         association table with (item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id,
         column_name, study_subject_id, activated) and no surrogate
         key. Had the precondition been correct, the DELETE would
         have raised `column "id" does not exist` at runtime. v1
         silently MARK_RAN'd in the field so this surface was never
         hit; both bugs were live.

    Net effect from v1: 16 rows persisted in dn_item_data_map and
    Subject-Matrix open-query counts stayed at 2× the intended value.

    Liquibase changeset-immutability convention (CLAUDE.md "Don't edit
    existing changesets") forbids correcting v1 in place. This v2:

      1. Precondition flipped — sqlCheck returns 1 when duplicates
         exist, expectedResult="1", so the precondition passes
         exactly when there's work to do.
      2. DELETE uses Postgres `ctid` (physical row identifier) to
         disambiguate the duplicate rows. ctid is well-defined for
         any heap row even without a declared key. dbms="postgresql"
         already gates the changeset to Postgres so `ctid` portability
         isn't a concern.

    Result: keep MIN(ctid) per (item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id,
    study_subject_id) tuple. The seed's inline rows arrive first
    (smaller ctid), the fixup re-inserts with larger ctid; keeping
    MIN(ctid) keeps the seed's row, consistent with "the seed is
    the source of truth".
  -->
<databaseChangeLog
    xmlns="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog
                        http://www.liquibase.org/xml/ns/dbchangelog/dbchangelog-3.6.xsd">

    <changeSet author="muw-ophthalmology" id="2026-06-02-prune-dn-item-data-map-duplicates-v2" dbms="postgresql">
        <preConditions onFail="MARK_RAN">
            <!-- Run when duplicates exist for any of the 8 seeded discrepancy notes.
                 sqlCheck returns 1 (= "duplicates present") → matches expectedResult="1"
                 → precondition passes → DELETE runs. When the table is clean the
                 check returns 0 → mismatch → MARK_RAN, no-op. -->
            <sqlCheck expectedResult="1">
                SELECT CASE WHEN COUNT(*) > COUNT(DISTINCT (item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id, study_subject_id))
                            THEN 1 ELSE 0 END
                FROM dn_item_data_map
                WHERE discrepancy_note_id BETWEEN 1 AND 8
            </sqlCheck>
        </preConditions>
        <comment>Drop duplicate dn_item_data_map rows for the 8 seeded discrepancy notes; keep MIN(ctid) per tuple (corrects v1 precondition + missing-column bugs)</comment>

        <sql splitStatements="false"><![CDATA[
            DELETE FROM dn_item_data_map
            WHERE ctid IN (
                SELECT ctid
                FROM (
                    SELECT ctid,
                           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
                               PARTITION BY item_data_id, discrepancy_note_id, study_subject_id
                               ORDER BY ctid
                           ) AS rn
                    FROM dn_item_data_map
                ) ranked
                WHERE ranked.rn > 1
            )
        ]]></sql>
    </changeSet>

</databaseChangeLog>
